  <Subject Subject_ID="300310193">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300251797</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>animal components [300251797], biological components [300265630], components by specific context [300241584], components (objects parts) [300241583], Components (hierarchy name) [300241490], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Parts of a human's or an animal's body, usually having fingers, located below the wrist joint of the arms, characterized by being routinely used for purposes other than support and locomotion. For the truncating components of legs, use "feet (animal components)," "paws (animal components)," "hooves (animal components)," or another appropriate term.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>人類或動物的身體部位，通常具有手指。手位於臂的腕關節下方；通常不用於支撐或移動身體。若是指腿的末端部位，則以「足(動物身體構造)」、「爪(動物身體構造)」、「蹄(動物身體構造)」或其他詞彙稱之。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Delen van het lichaam van een mens of een dier, gewoonlijk met vingers, die zich bevinden onder het polsgewricht van de armen en zich kenmerken doordat ze normaliter gebruikt worden voor andere doeleinden dan steun en voortbeweging. Gebruik 'voeten (dierlijke lichaamsdelen)', 'klauwen (dierlijke lichaamsdelen)', 'hoeven (dierlijke lichaamsdelen)' of een andere passende term voor de uiteinden van poten of benen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Teil eines menschlichen oder tierischen Körpers am Handgelenk des Armes, in der Regel mit Fingern, üblicherwiese gekennzeichnet durch die Nutzung für andere Aufgaben als Stehen oder Fortbewegen. Für das entsprechende, abschließende Körperteil am Bein ist "Fuß (tierische und menschliche Komponenten)", "Pfote (tierische und menschliche Komponenten))", "Huf (tierische und menschliche Komponenten)" oder einen anderer geeigneten Begriff zu verwenden.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Partes del cuerpo de un humano o un animal, que suelen tener dedos, situadas debajo de la articulación de la muñeca de los brazos, caracterizadas por ser utilizadas rutinariamente para fines distintos del apoyo y la locomoción. Para los componentes troncales de las piernas, utilice "feet (animal components)," "paws (animal components)," "hooves (animal components)," u otro término apropiado.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Achi tlacayoliztli tlen macehualli zo tecuani, tlen quipiya imahpil huan eltoc ica echcapan tlen tomaomiyo tlen toamacayo, momanextia pampa tlahuel motequihuia para mocui zo moitzquia ce tlamantli. Para tlen motzquitoc ica tometz, xictequihui "feet (animal components)," "paws (animal components)," "hooves (animal components)," zo xictequihui ceyoc tlahtolli tlen quinamiqui.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Eastern Huasteca Nahuatl</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
